This paper is about improving the performance of indoor semantic segmentation using a novel neural network architecture that incorporates depth information. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) applications, which are both subcategories of CS. The paper also involves machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which are closely related to CV and RO. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (MM) data (RGB-D images), which is another relevant subcategory of CS. Therefore, the most likely subcategory is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
